your job is to create sensible bead tasks from this description:
create a bash script called main.sh that calls all scripts in the scripts directory then sleep for 30 minutes. do this in an endless Loop.
in the scripts directory create the following scripts:
- update_fixer.sh: loops through all repositories in the repo directory (adjustable via config located in the root directory of this repository) and does in a Loop over all renovate branches the following:
  - git fetch
  - git reset --hard
  - git clean
  - make test: if this command fails run opencode cli with the instruction to fix the branch that contains updates to dependecnies und push them to the branch
- update.sh: creates a directory in this repository for each repo in the repo directory. the names should be equal
- planner.sh :
    - checks for each repository in the repo directory a corresponding directory in this repository exists. if so iterate over all files in this directory. here is what to do:
        - grab all files that do not end with a number that is higher than a number that is configured in the settings of this repository
        - go to the repository for this directory and switch to the branch ai
        - grab the content of the file and start the opencode cli with the command to tell it to generate bead tasks for whatever is written in the file.
        - increment the number at the end of the filename (add ".1" if there is no number)
        - commit and push all changes made in this repository
